cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.HC, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new way of modeling social graphs and examines social relationships at scale using an online platform. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is also likely as the paper describes the design of an online platform for data collection. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is relevant as the paper draws on sociological and social psychological literature to identify dimensions of social relationships. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the practical implications of the proposed model for the design of social-networking applications. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves natural language processing in the analysis of people's descriptions of their relationships.
